JioFi M2 Revival Kit — third-party components and attribution
=============================================================

This project bundles and builds on the work of others. Their licenses and
attribution are preserved here as required. Only revive.ps1 and the
documentation are original to this repository (MIT, see LICENSE).

1. qtools  (qdload, qrflash, qwdirect, qbadblock, qcommand, qefs, qnvram, ...)
   Author:  forth32
   Source:  https://github.com/forth32/qtools
   License: GNU GPL v3 — full text in qtool/LICENSE, original readme in
            qtool/README.md. Redistributed unmodified.

2. Patched "peek"/streaming NAND loaders (loaders/ENPRG9x07p.mbn,
   ENPRG9x45p.bin, NPRG9x45p.bin, etc.)
   Origin:  bkerler's Loaders collection
   Source:  https://github.com/bkerler/Loaders
   These low-level programmers are what allow the NAND controller to be
   initialised correctly on MDM9x07 hardware.

3. Device firmware images (images/*.oob)
   These are Reliance Jio / JioFi M2 proprietary firmware, dumped from a
   physical device. They are NOT included in this repository. They are the
   property of their respective rights holders and are distributed only as a
   convenience within the hobbyist repair community. If you are a rights
   holder and want them removed from any mirror, that request will be honored.

4. EFS2 / device-identity data
   Intentionally NOT included. EFS2 carries a device's IMEI and RF
   calibration. Publishing it would publish a real IMEI. See README for the
   own-IMEI-only policy.

Thanks to sheikhshahnawaz41299 for the JioFi M2 Ver-2 firmware backups and
tools that helped make this kit possible.

The Qualcomm IMEI-writing tool referenced in the disaster-recovery flow is
NOT included in this repository for legal reasons; obtain it yourself only for
restoring your own device's original IMEI.
